# [ANIMA](../wg/anima.html)

## Summary
The ANIMA Working Group (WG) met at IETF 126 to discuss the status of active working group documents, review progress on constrained environment drafts, and explore a major proposed recharter to support AI-powered network agents (Agentic AI) and intent-based autonomic networking. The WG has successfully advanced several core BRSKI specifications through the IESG, freeing up cycles for new work. Key discussions centered on constrained BRSKI (cBRSKI), constrained GRASP (cGRASP), autonomic traffic management in AI Data Centers, AI-powered Autonomic Service Agents (AI-ASAs), GRASP routing issues, and security boundaries for AI agent network admission.

