### 2. Constrained BRSKI (cBRSKI) and Join Proxy
* **Presenter**: Esko Dijk
* **Slides**: [01 cBRSKI and Join Proxy](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-anima-cbrski-and-join-proxy-00)
* **Associated Drafts**:
  * `draft-ietf-anima-constrained-voucher`
  * `draft-ietf-anima-constrained-join-proxy`
* **cBRSKI (Voucher) Updates**:
  * Aligned the join proxy discovery mechanism with the updated CoAP link format discovery, resulting in smaller, simpler message sizes.
  * Added DTLS 1.2 and DTLS 1.3 cipher suite details to establish a baseline for interoperability.
  * Esko demonstrated a simulated end-to-end onboarding chain at the IETF Hackathon using a virtual Thread mesh network (IPv6-based) connected to Java-based web services.
  * Following a detailed Shepherd review, Esko proposed leaving "device management after onboarding" out of scope for this document to keep the draft focused. This work may be picked up in other groups (e.g., ACE or LAMPS).
* **Constrained Join Proxy Updates**:
  * Adopted updated onboarding terminology.
  * Provided stricter guidance on mode selection (stateless vs. stateful).
  * Refined the definition of the `JPY` URI scheme.
  * Shortened discovery message sizes in coordination with the CORE WG.

